1
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:13,167
<i>Let's talk and settle things,
once and for all.</i>

2
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:14,533
<i> Let's meet tomorrow.</i>

3
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:16,000
<i>Do you know why
I believed Jade?</i>

4
00:00:16,133 --> 00:00:17,533
<i> Because she used Mookie!</i>

5
00:00:17,667 --> 00:00:18,433
<i> Hi.</i>

6
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:20,033
<i> You're both here.</i>

7
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:21,233
<i> Let me please...</i>

8
00:00:21,367 --> 00:00:23,733
<i>I will prove that you caused me
my mental condition.</i>

9
00:00:23,867 --> 00:00:26,000
<i> I know you do not love Mookie!</i>

10
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:28,133
<i>You just want to ruin our
family!</i>

11
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:31,333
<i>I don't have to try to do
that to you and your family.</i>

12
00:00:31,467 --> 00:00:35,267
<i>Because you did that
all by yourself!</i>

13
00:00:35,433 --> 00:00:36,933
<i> Don't worry.</i>

14
00:00:37,067 --> 00:00:40,367
<i>Because I'll make you feel what
you made me go through.</i>

15
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:41,267
<i> You know what that's called?</i>

16
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:43,300
<i> Karma.</i>

17
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:48,533
<i>You, me, and your dad are
going on a staycation!</i>

18
00:00:48,667 --> 00:00:49,633
<i> Does that mean...</i>

19
00:00:50,767 --> 00:00:52,533
<i>This would be my first family
outing!</i>

20
00:00:52,667 --> 00:00:55,433
<i> Thank you, Mommy Jade!</i>

21
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:38,033
Emma?

22
00:01:39,133 --> 00:01:41,467
Do you want to rest in
the office for a while?

23
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:46,933
No, Flor. I am not tired.

24
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,533
I am just sad.

25
00:01:49,667 --> 00:01:53,967
Mookie blocked me
on social media.

26
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:58,200
I can't see how she is doing
or what she's up to.

27
00:01:59,333 --> 00:02:00,833
Is that all?

28
00:02:00,967 --> 00:02:02,033
Don't worry!

29
00:02:02,167 --> 00:02:03,633
I got you!

30
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,833
Look.

31
00:02:06,967 --> 00:02:08,333
View her using my account.

32
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:09,167
Go!

33
00:02:17,133 --> 00:02:21,033
Oh, in fairness to
our Baby Mookie!

34
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:24,167
She had a glow-up.
She looks so pretty!

35
00:02:25,967 --> 00:02:31,300
But that does not matter
if she is surrounded by stress!

36
00:02:33,667 --> 00:02:35,433
"First family vacation."

37
00:02:37,867 --> 00:02:39,233
Oh, yes.

38
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:43,467
But the real mother
is not there.

39
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:49,267
Jade planned to get my family.

40
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:52,033
But I should be there.

41
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,567
And that is the perfect place

42
00:02:56,700 --> 00:03:00,033
to start my plan of taking
Mookie back.

43
00:03:00,167 --> 00:03:03,467
And let Jade snap back into the
reality that they are my family.

44
00:03:48,267 --> 00:03:54,567
One big happy family!

45
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:01,367
With Emma out of the equation,

46
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:05,333
you will finally be happy
together with Mookie and Danilo.

47
00:04:07,667 --> 00:04:10,400
I know, right?

48
00:04:10,533 --> 00:04:16,500
Life is so much better without
Emma!

49
00:04:16,633 --> 00:04:18,133
Look at that!

50
00:04:26,067 --> 00:04:27,700
You're too loud!

51
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:30,867
Please!

52
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,367
Save that noise for another day.

53
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:38,333
Because Danilo, Mookie and I
will have a grand vacation.

54
00:04:38,467 --> 00:04:39,933
Don't worry.

55
00:04:40,067 --> 00:04:43,933
Someone will watch over
you while we're away.

56
00:04:44,067 --> 00:04:44,800
Okay?

57
00:04:48,467 --> 00:04:51,633
My family.

58
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:03,033
Oh, finally, love!

59
00:05:03,167 --> 00:05:06,067
We can finally spend some
vacation time together!

60
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,733
- Hi, miss.
- Hi.

61
00:05:07,867 --> 00:05:12,267
-Reservation under Jade Caparas.
-Okay.

62
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:14,367
This place is beautiful.

63
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:15,733
- Right?
- Yeah.

64
00:05:15,867 --> 00:05:19,000
But Jade, you don't really have
to do this.

65
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,233
Hi, guys!

66
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:23,167
Hey, what's that?

67
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:25,167
- Say hi!
- Live? Live?

68
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:27,767
Welcome to Dream Resort
Paradiso!

69
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:29,033
We are here,

70
00:05:29,167 --> 00:05:33,633
and I am so excited to share
more stories with you, guys!

71
00:05:35,467 --> 00:05:38,067
Of course, all the best for
Mookie.

72
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,800
And of course, for you, love.

73
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:42,467
- Thank you, Mommy Jade!
- Thank you.

74
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,933
By the way, where are your
friends?

75
00:05:44,067 --> 00:05:45,300
I thought they were going with
us?

76
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:48,433
Mommy Jade, they will be here in
a few hours.

77
00:05:48,567 --> 00:05:51,367
I'm glad they still had
their rooms reserved.

78
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:52,533
That's good!

79
00:05:52,667 --> 00:05:54,633
I am so excited to see them
again.

80
00:05:55,767 --> 00:05:58,800
But please refrain from doing
foolish things, okay?

81
00:05:58,933 --> 00:06:00,267
Of course, Dad!

82
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:01,400
Promise!

83
00:06:01,533 --> 00:06:04,000
Mookie is actually a good girl.

84
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:05,667
That's a promise, okay?

85
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:08,367
Wow, they even serve
us refreshments!

86
00:06:08,533 --> 00:06:09,500
I love it!

87
00:06:09,633 --> 00:06:11,267
Love, this is for you.

88
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:12,100
Thank you.

89
00:06:12,233 --> 00:06:14,233
Mookie, this is for you.

90
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:15,933
Thank you, mommy.

91
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,567
Sorry, I got this first.

92
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:22,267
And so does the man
you are going to marry.

93
00:06:24,733 --> 00:06:25,500
Emma?

94
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:29,200
What a coincidence!

95
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:30,700
You're here!

96
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:32,967
Coincidence your face!

97
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:36,833
How are you, Mookie?

98
00:06:37,967 --> 00:06:39,933
She's fine.

99
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:42,933
So, what are you doing here?

100
00:06:44,633 --> 00:06:48,500
I'm here to get an X-ray
and some blood tests.

101
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:49,433
Joke!

102
00:06:51,033 --> 00:06:51,767
How dumb!

103
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:56,433
Of course, we are on vacation!

104
00:06:56,567 --> 00:06:57,733
Staycation!

105
00:06:57,867 --> 00:07:00,067
This is a resort, after all!

106
00:07:02,767 --> 00:07:04,000
You're so funny!

107
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:06,700
You know what, Emma,

108
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:11,100
if you are just here to ruin
our vacation, just leave.

109
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:13,700
Leave?

110
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:18,533
Why would we leave if the owners
of this place are our friends?

111
00:07:18,667 --> 00:07:20,100
Right, miss?

112
00:07:20,233 --> 00:07:22,067
Yes, Mr. Alvarez.

113
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:24,733
Your VIP room is ready for you.

114
00:07:24,867 --> 00:07:25,800
What was that?

115
00:07:25,933 --> 00:07:27,000
VIP?

116
00:07:27,133 --> 00:07:27,633
Yes, sir.

117
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:29,533
Did you hear that?

118
00:07:31,067 --> 00:07:32,033
VIP.

119
00:07:32,167 --> 00:07:35,167
That means we have
a bigger room.

120
00:07:36,133 --> 00:07:40,800
Meaning, suite!

121
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:43,300
Sweet, indeed!

122
00:07:43,433 --> 00:07:46,633
Just like a castle.
For my Queen. Right?

123
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:48,667
Awesome!

124
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,267
Hi, Mookie.

125
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:53,600
Hi, Flor.

126
00:07:56,533 --> 00:07:59,300
Mr. Alvarez, your VIP room
is ready for you.

127
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,300
It's just about right.

128
00:08:03,367 --> 00:08:04,267
Did you hear that again?

129
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,500
Enjoy your standard room.

130
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:16,733
Out of all the resorts,
why does it have to be here?

131
00:08:16,867 --> 00:08:18,700
I will cancel our reservation!

132
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:20,133
We will go to another resort!

133
00:08:20,267 --> 00:08:22,800
I saw another one nearby.

134
00:08:22,967 --> 00:08:25,133
I think they have better
facilities.

135
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:26,167
This is cheap!

136
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:27,500
We will not leave!

137
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:28,167
What?

138
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:29,167
We will stay here.

139
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:33,200
If we leave,
we will look like losers!

140
00:08:33,333 --> 00:08:35,800
And why should we be affected?

141
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:39,067
We are here for a vacation,
for family bonding.

142
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:42,567
Don't let them ruin
our vacation.

143
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,600
Fine.

144
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:45,933
Miss,

145
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:48,233
can you upgrade our room
into a super suite?

146
00:08:48,367 --> 00:08:50,700
Sorry, ma'am.
We are fully booked.

147
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:52,900
Your junior suite is ready
for you.

148
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:55,500
Fine!

149
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:56,500
We'll take that!

150
00:08:57,933 --> 00:08:58,433
Let's go!

151
00:08:58,567 --> 00:08:59,500
Let's go.

152
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:03,700
This place is beautiful!

153
00:09:05,467 --> 00:09:08,500
Emma, did you see Jade's face?

154
00:09:08,633 --> 00:09:11,133
She was so annoyed.

155
00:09:11,267 --> 00:09:14,833
It was also evident
that Danilo was jealous.

156
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:18,367
I think he regrets leaving you.

157
00:09:19,567 --> 00:09:20,233
Wait a minute.

158
00:09:21,633 --> 00:09:23,667
- Wait a minute.
- All right.

159
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:24,500
Hello?

160
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:26,767
I will look for a better
reception.

161
00:09:31,933 --> 00:09:32,567
Emma,

162
00:09:34,067 --> 00:09:36,467
I have an innocent question.

163
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:40,433
Do you still have feelings
for Danilo?

164
00:09:43,133 --> 00:09:50,733
Will Mookie get closer to me if
Danilo switches to my side.

165
00:09:50,867 --> 00:09:51,600
And one more thing,

166
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:53,267
I want to take revenge on Jade

167
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,200
for taking my family away from
me.

168
00:09:57,300 --> 00:09:58,733
Is that for real?

169
00:10:00,967 --> 00:10:05,267
Are you sure there's nothing
left in your heart for Danilo?

170
00:10:06,367 --> 00:10:07,333
Nothing more.

171
00:10:07,467 --> 00:10:08,933
I just want Mookie back.

172
00:10:09,067 --> 00:10:12,533
I am doing all this for Mookie.

173
00:10:12,667 --> 00:10:14,433
She's all I have left.

174
00:10:14,567 --> 00:10:16,400
And I don't want to lose her.

175
00:10:18,033 --> 00:10:19,633
If you say so.

176
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:23,667
Look at our photos.

177
00:10:25,767 --> 00:10:28,100
Can I talk to you for a moment?

178
00:10:30,467 --> 00:10:31,433
Mookie?

179
00:10:32,867 --> 00:10:35,600
Okay, I will give you both
some time together.

180
00:10:35,767 --> 00:10:36,400
I'll go over there.

181
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:39,333
It's nice to see you again,
Flor.

182
00:10:39,467 --> 00:10:41,233
Nice to see you also!

183
00:10:42,233 --> 00:10:43,167
I'll go ahead.

184
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:44,567
Bye, Mookie!

185
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:46,300
Mookie...

186
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:50,500
I just have a request.

187
00:10:50,633 --> 00:10:51,833
What? Anything!

188
00:10:52,967 --> 00:10:54,900
I'm glad you agreed to talk.

189
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:58,600
Can you please stay away from
us?

190
00:11:00,433 --> 00:11:05,367
Or maybe I need to do something
for you to stop bothering us?

191
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:06,267
Mookie...

192
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:09,967
You know I cannot do that!

193
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:11,733
I love you so much!

194
00:11:11,867 --> 00:11:13,767
I cannot stay away from you.

195
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:17,533
Love?

196
00:11:18,567 --> 00:11:19,667
You love me?

197
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:25,667
If you really love me,
you would not have left.

198
00:11:26,667 --> 00:11:27,967
You would have come back!

199
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:30,600
You should not have been
with that guy!

200
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:37,700
You would not have chosen
another man over me

201
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:40,000
and my dad if you loved me!

202
00:11:40,133 --> 00:11:44,000
Mookie, I cannot choose anyone
over you.

203
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:45,933
You are my life!

204
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:48,967
Really?

205
00:11:54,867 --> 00:11:56,400
I do not need you anymore.

206
00:11:58,633 --> 00:12:02,700
Mommy Jade and Daddy
are getting married soon.

207
00:12:02,833 --> 00:12:05,267
We will become a happy family.

208
00:12:06,033 --> 00:12:11,767
So please, please,
stay away from us.

209
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,433
That's all I ever wanted
from you.

210
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:14,567
That cannot be, Mookie.

211
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:15,500
Mookie!

212
00:12:15,633 --> 00:12:16,667
Mookie?

213
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:30,033
Are you sure it's okay
that Cacai and I are here?

214
00:12:30,767 --> 00:12:34,200
I thought this was your first
vacation as a family?

215
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:39,033
Hey, Mookie already said she
is happier when she is with us.

216
00:12:39,167 --> 00:12:43,733
Or maybe she is happier
when you are with her.

217
00:12:44,133 --> 00:12:45,633
Does she look happy to you?

218
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,667
Oh my.

219
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,000
I'll just take selfies
over there...

220
00:12:50,167 --> 00:12:51,967
in a far, far away area.

221
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:53,867
I will leave you both here.

222
00:12:58,267 --> 00:12:59,167
Zayn,

223
00:13:00,933 --> 00:13:02,200
am I a bad daughter?

224
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:04,900
Why would you say that?

225
00:13:05,033 --> 00:13:07,000
I just feel guilty about
the things

226
00:13:07,133 --> 00:13:08,833
that I said to Mommy Emma.

227
00:13:08,967 --> 00:13:12,667
But I needed to say that so she
would stop doing these things.

228
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:15,367
I just don't want her
and Mommy Jade to fight.

229
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:18,467
I think it's not good
that they fight.

230
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,767
Daddy gets affected too.

231
00:13:23,367 --> 00:13:24,667
So tell me, Zayn...

232
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:29,867
Am I a bad daughter for telling
my mom to leave us alone?

233
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,767
Do you want an honest answer?

234
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:35,300
I did not expect that you could
say that.

235
00:13:36,467 --> 00:13:42,033
If I were your mom,
I would be shocked and hurt.

236
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:44,833
Oh well.

237
00:13:46,567 --> 00:13:50,800
I just don't want to see her
with Logan.

238
00:13:50,933 --> 00:13:54,867
I remember the day when
she left us and chose him.

239
00:13:58,367 --> 00:14:04,033
But why do I feel this way?

240
00:14:04,167 --> 00:14:05,900
I pity her.

241
00:14:06,033 --> 00:14:08,400
I still get hurt when she's
hurt.

242
00:14:09,667 --> 00:14:13,133
You know what, when I get
into a fight with my mom,

243
00:14:13,267 --> 00:14:14,700
I just get quiet.

244
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:18,233
But I am also hurt when
I know that I am hurting her.

245
00:14:18,367 --> 00:14:19,667
Because I love my mom.

246
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:24,800
No matter how angry you get
at your mom,

247
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:26,600
I'm sure you still love her.

248
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:36,800
I can take everything
that Jade will tell me.

249
00:14:36,933 --> 00:14:40,200
But I cannot take what Mookie
said to me earlier.

250
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:45,733
They are telling her what to do.
I know.

251
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,267
You are right.

252
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:52,967
They poisoned my daughter's
mind.

253
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:55,467
So I have to make it up to her.

254
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:59,367
Your daughter is disrespectful.

255
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:00,400
If I were her father,

256
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:01,933
she's really gonna get it.

257
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:05,033
Please choose your words
when it comes to Mookie.

258
00:15:06,167 --> 00:15:07,633
She is still my daughter.

259
00:15:07,767 --> 00:15:12,567
She may shout at me and hurt me,
but I will never stop trying.

260
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:15,133
And until I get my revenge
on Jade.

261
00:15:15,267 --> 00:15:16,033
Emma?

262
00:15:16,167 --> 00:15:16,933
Emma!

263
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,400
Look at that.

264
00:15:22,433 --> 00:15:25,067
I heard at the reception

265
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:29,100
that Jade asked for a poolside
setup for her and Danilo.

266
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:30,300
Maybe that's it.

267
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:33,733
I think the gazebo in the middle
looks too good.

268
00:15:37,767 --> 00:15:39,667
I know what you're thinking.

269
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,200
This will be fun.

270
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:56,000
Ma'am, this way, please.

271
00:15:56,133 --> 00:15:57,767
Thank you.

272
00:15:59,567 --> 00:16:00,467
Oh, wow!

273
00:16:00,933 --> 00:16:02,533
How lovely!

274
00:16:02,667 --> 00:16:05,333
Ma'am, this is the place you
reserved.

275
00:16:05,467 --> 00:16:06,233
Perfect.

276
00:16:06,367 --> 00:16:07,233
Thank you!

277
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:08,800
Thank you.

278
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:13,567
Why is there a setup
at the other gazebo?

279
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:15,600
Who...

280
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:21,300
Emma?

281
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,900
Don't tell me

282
00:16:24,033 --> 00:16:26,133
that you are also going
to have dinner here as well?

283
00:16:29,767 --> 00:16:30,567
Why?

284
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:34,300
Is this your place?

285
00:16:34,433 --> 00:16:38,933
And you are not the only one who
wants to eat beside the pool.

286
00:16:42,100 --> 00:16:45,733
Why don't I just push you
into the pool?

287
00:16:45,867 --> 00:16:48,133
So you could swim as well.

288
00:16:48,267 --> 00:16:51,600
Jade, please stop this.
It's embarrassing.

289
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,333
People can see us.

290
00:16:55,367 --> 00:16:57,633
Please cancel our
reservation here.

291
00:16:57,767 --> 00:17:00,233
We will just eat
at the restaurant.

292
00:17:00,367 --> 00:17:01,533
You did not inform me

293
00:17:01,667 --> 00:17:03,767
that your pool doesn't just
smell of chlorine.

294
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:06,700
It also reeks of stinky plastic.

295
00:17:08,867 --> 00:17:09,367
Enough.

296
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:10,467
Why are you avoiding?

297
00:17:11,967 --> 00:17:14,000
There are only two options.

298
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:18,967
Either our presence bothers you,
or you are just insecure.

299
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:22,300
Don't be so full of yourself.

300
00:17:22,433 --> 00:17:27,467
Emma, I will never be insecure
with someone like you.

301
00:17:30,567 --> 00:17:33,700
Fine, we'll keep
the reservation.

302
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:37,033
Let's have a double date.

303
00:17:37,167 --> 00:17:40,067
Whoever stays
away is a coward.

304
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:44,667
Whoever gets annoyed is big
loser.

305
00:18:00,667 --> 00:18:01,900
I wonder where Mookie is.

306
00:18:02,033 --> 00:18:02,867
Yeah.

307
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,367
We've been looking
for her for a while.

308
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:07,700
Maybe she's just getting ready.

309
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:12,000
Guys, sorry, I'm late.

310
00:18:25,933 --> 00:18:27,600
Are you amazed?

311
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:29,133
Close your mouth!

312
00:18:30,367 --> 00:18:33,633
Yeah. Why are you speechless?

313
00:18:33,767 --> 00:18:36,600
I'm just really happy...

314
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:39,967
that you are slowly getting
things back together.

315
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:41,367
The Mookie that I once liked.

316
00:18:42,933 --> 00:18:46,333
This is my cue to leave.

317
00:18:47,767 --> 00:18:50,133
Stay here!

318
00:18:50,267 --> 00:18:52,600
I think I am getting in the way.

319
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:56,367
Just look at how he looks
at you.

320
00:18:59,267 --> 00:19:00,833
I just have to ask...

321
00:19:01,867 --> 00:19:04,233
Don't you want to see
the Rebel Mookie again?

322
00:19:05,367 --> 00:19:08,733
You did change when you
and Aunt Jade got close.

323
00:19:09,933 --> 00:19:11,267
You were already a snob,

324
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,467
then you became short-tempered,
too.

325
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:16,167
And you have lost the thing I
liked most about you as well.

326
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:19,200
Liked most?

327
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:20,567
Your smile.

328
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:25,933
You looked happier when you were
under Aunt Emma's care.

329
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:30,200
I am still the same old happy
girl.

330
00:19:31,433 --> 00:19:32,967
I just had a rebellious stage

331
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:36,067
because I was really annoyed
with my mom.

332
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:39,333
But now, I feel like I am
getting happier again

333
00:19:39,467 --> 00:19:42,467
because my dad and Mommy
Jade will get married soon.

334
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:51,867
But you have not brought back
the old smile that you've got.

335
00:19:53,033 --> 00:19:58,933
And I think you will only
get that smile back

336
00:19:59,067 --> 00:20:01,200
when you're with Aunt Emma
again.

337
00:20:24,667 --> 00:20:27,033
Perfect! Thank you!

338
00:20:27,167 --> 00:20:29,200
Love, try this.

339
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,700
Here you go.

340
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,100
Try it.

341
00:20:39,033 --> 00:20:40,200
Go ahead try it.

342
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:43,733
I don't...

343
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:45,033
You don't like it?

344
00:20:46,433 --> 00:20:48,133
He is allergic to that!

345
00:20:53,667 --> 00:20:54,733
Fine.

346
00:20:54,867 --> 00:20:56,300
Try this one.

347
00:20:56,433 --> 00:20:58,000
Have this orange juice.

348
00:20:58,133 --> 00:21:01,400
This is freshly squeezed.
So it's healthy and safe.

349
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:08,033
Are you okay, love?

350
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,133
Are you okay?

351
00:21:09,267 --> 00:21:11,533
He does not take cold drinks.

352
00:21:11,667 --> 00:21:13,000
He wants them warm.

353
00:21:13,133 --> 00:21:15,033
What kind of engagement do you
have?

354
00:21:15,167 --> 00:21:16,367
You still do not know each other
that well.

355
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,833
You may be right.

356
00:21:19,967 --> 00:21:24,233
But maybe you should not
tell me how I should care

357
00:21:24,367 --> 00:21:25,900
for my fiancé.

358
00:21:27,267 --> 00:21:28,167
Girls!

359
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:29,767
Girls!

360
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:33,833
Come on.
Don't treat Danilo like a baby!

361
00:21:33,967 --> 00:21:36,300
He's an adult.

362
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:38,833
A bit immature, maybe.

363
00:21:38,967 --> 00:21:41,467
Don't you dare call me that.

364
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,333
We are not close.

365
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:49,433
Just eat, love.

366
00:21:49,567 --> 00:21:50,767
Bro...

367
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:54,267
Logan, I just want to remind
you...

368
00:21:54,767 --> 00:21:58,533
Even if you serve a new
dish to someone,

369
00:21:59,467 --> 00:22:02,900
that person will still look for
the old ones he's used to.

370
00:22:03,033 --> 00:22:07,767
Oh, the dish he spat out
because it did not taste good?

371
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:09,467
The one dish he spat out,

372
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:13,067
but then he realized
that he still liked it better.

373
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:16,167
Right, Dan?

374
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:23,400
Please mind your own man!

375
00:22:23,533 --> 00:22:26,667
Do not stare into someone
else's fiancé!

376
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:29,333
Why would Emma do that?

377
00:22:29,467 --> 00:22:32,333
I am here in front of her.
Right, Ems?

378
00:22:32,467 --> 00:22:35,433
Fiancé that you took
from someone else.

379
00:22:35,567 --> 00:22:38,300
And for the record,
Logan is just a friend.

380
00:22:38,767 --> 00:22:42,900
Friends, soon-to-be lovers.

381
00:22:43,033 --> 00:22:44,233
Please stop.

382
00:22:46,067 --> 00:22:50,333
Oh, the type of friends who
flirt with each other!

383
00:22:51,433 --> 00:22:52,833
I said that's enough!

384
00:23:00,367 --> 00:23:01,433
Dan...

385
00:23:03,267 --> 00:23:04,833
You are now hot headed.

386
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:06,900
You were not like that before.

387
00:23:07,033 --> 00:23:09,433
Maybe something's missing.

388
00:23:09,567 --> 00:23:10,367
Like what?

389
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:12,400
Don't worry, Jade.

390
00:23:12,533 --> 00:23:15,200
I will not do anything
to Danilo.

391
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:16,600
I am just winking at him.

392
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:27,133
Emma, let's go.
This is not fun anymore.

393
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:31,700
Logan, we are not losers.

394
00:23:33,433 --> 00:23:37,333
You know what, Logan,
she will not come with you.

395
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:40,867
Because she is not done
her plan yet.

396
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:48,133
See? She's so desperate that
she's intervening with our date.

397
00:23:48,267 --> 00:23:49,933
Who are you calling desperate?

398
00:23:50,067 --> 00:23:51,800
When you are the bug

399
00:23:51,933 --> 00:23:53,833
who squeezed yourself
into our lives!

400
00:23:53,967 --> 00:23:56,367
And chewed our relationship
away!

401
00:23:56,533 --> 00:24:00,733
Of all the men in the world,
you really chose my husband!

402
00:24:00,867 --> 00:24:01,867
Your husband?

403
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:05,100
You were not even married!

404
00:24:05,233 --> 00:24:07,900
Don't be delusional!

405
00:24:08,033 --> 00:24:09,633
Feeling legal wife!

406
00:24:11,567 --> 00:24:13,433
You are not yet married.

407
00:24:13,567 --> 00:24:15,633
A lot of things can still
happen.

408
00:24:15,767 --> 00:24:18,567
And remember this,
we have a daughter.

409
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:20,767
A daughter who hates you
so much!

410
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:22,700
Please stop this!

411
00:24:22,833 --> 00:24:24,233
If things will be like this,

412
00:24:24,367 --> 00:24:26,100
let us just go our separate
ways!

413
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:29,233
- He's mad.
- Let's go!

414
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,500
Ma'am, Sir,

415
00:24:30,633 --> 00:24:35,433
we prepared a game for a more
exciting dinner tonight.

416
00:24:35,567 --> 00:24:37,800
Mat game with a twist.

417
00:24:37,933 --> 00:24:38,933
Are you game?

418
00:24:39,067 --> 00:24:40,433
- Game!
- Of course, I'm in.

419
00:24:41,667 --> 00:24:45,833
Same, game.
How about you?

420
00:24:53,267 --> 00:24:55,333
Why do I feel this way?

421
00:24:55,467 --> 00:25:00,300
Why am I still hoping
that she will come back to us?

422
00:25:00,433 --> 00:25:02,867
I want to hug her again!

423
00:25:03,033 --> 00:25:04,667
I want to talk to her.

424
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:08,067
I want us to get back
to how we used to be.

425
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:10,567
I wish Mookie knows the truth.

426
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:12,767
You cannot blame her.

427
00:25:12,900 --> 00:25:16,533
It's really hard to believe that
you and Logan are just friends.

428
00:25:16,667 --> 00:25:19,833
You live in the same house.

429
00:25:19,967 --> 00:25:21,233
Why are you so quiet?

430
00:25:21,367 --> 00:25:23,767
There must be something going on
in your mind.

431
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:25,233
Don't fool me.

432
00:25:25,367 --> 00:25:26,867
Don't make me look like a fool,
either!

433
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:28,133
What is your problem?

434
00:25:28,267 --> 00:25:32,567
Do you really want to get
Mookie back, or Danilo too?

435
00:25:32,700 --> 00:25:36,000
I will do everything
to take Mookie back.

436
00:25:36,167 --> 00:25:37,067
What?

437
00:25:38,633 --> 00:25:38,900
What are you doing?
